README

train.py
train.py trains the neural network such that it can transfer the style of one picture to another, creating a new picture.
The code is inspired from the tutorial "How_to_do_style_transfer_in_tensorflow" (link).

Example of command-line prompt:

python3 train_test.py --in-path ./images/mcgill.jpg --out-path ./ --style-path ./images/canada.jpg --file-name result_canada --iterations-nbr 200


Flags:

--in-path: 		Path to file to transform.
--out-path:		Destination (dir or file) of transformed file or files.
--style-path:	File with style to use
--file-name:		Name of file to be saved
--iterations-nbr:	Number of iterations before output result

Note: --in-path, --out-path, --style-path and --file-name are mandatory arguments.
